learning_outcomes.en:
By the end of this course, students are able to:

1)	describe, differentiate, criticise and apply major traditional and critical approaches to security;
2)	contextualise contemporary security theories vis-à-vis earlier theoretical traditions and argumentations;
3)	critically read and analyse theoretical texts as well as apply them for examining practical research questions in their own research;
4)	apply reflective skills to practical problem solving in contemporary security scene.

During the course, students will develop their: 
1)	reading skills, ability to digest and criticise theoretical arguments; 
2)	writing skills through composing a research paper; 
3)	reflective skills by critically evaluating and synthesising competing conceptions and theories of security as well as applying them to contemporary security challenges.

learning_outcomes.et:
Kursuse lõpuks peaksid osalejad:

1) suutma kirjeldada, eristada, arvustada ja rakendada peamisi traditsioonilisi ja kriitilisi lähenemisi julgeoleku analüüsimisel;
2) oskama suhestada kaasaegseid julgeolekupoliitika teooria arenguid varasemate julgeolekupoliitiliste argumentatsioonidega;
3) valdama teoreetiliste tekstide kriitilise lugemise ja analüüsi oskust praktiliste uurimisküsimuste lahendamisel.

Kursus arendab:

1) akadeemilise eneseväljenduse ja debateerimise oskust seminaride kaudu;
2) akadeemilise kirjutamise oskust uurimistöö kirjutamise kaudu;
3) julgeolekuprobleemide teoreetilise mõtestamise ning praktiliste lahendustega seostamise oskust.
